Quick start to using the ircbot
===============================

To compile everything run:

 make

Then to start an Erlang REPL shell, with the path set to the .beam files, run:

 make run-shell

Once in the Erlang REPL you can start the bot with:

 Pid = ircbot_main:start(["irc.freenode.net", 6667, "erlbot_test", ["#erlbot_test"]]). 
 Pid ! {send_data, "PRIVMSG #erlbot_test :success"}.
 % To load some plugins
 gen_event:add_handler(plugins, 'plugins.rps', []).
 gen_event:add_handler(plugins, 'plugins.tell', []).

If you make changes to some plugin, while the bot is still running, just 
hit "make" again (in another terminal) and then back in the erlang REPL run:

 l('plugins.rps').

Erlangs code switching and gen_event framework will handle all the details to
run the new code without even disconnecting.
